 living species. Combining these data with molecular sequences, we obtained a phylogenetic tree that, when calibrated with fossils, shows that crown clade Placentalia and placental orders originated after the K-Pg boundary. Many nodes discovered using molecular data are upheld, but phenomic signals overturn molecular signals to show Sundatheria (Dermoptera + Scandentia) as the sister taxon of Primates, a close link between Proboscidea (elephants) and Sirenia (sea cows), and the monophyly of echolocating Chiroptera (bats). Our tree suggests that Placentalia first split into Xenarthra and Epitheria; extinct New World species are the oldest members of Afrotheria.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "O'Leary, Maureen A.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Bloch, Jonathan I.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Flynn, John J.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Gaudin, Timothy J.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Giallombardo, Andres", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Giannini, Norberto P.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Goldberg, Suzann L.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Kraatz, Brian P.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Luo, Zhe-Xi", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Meng, Jin", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Ni, Xijun", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Novacek, Michael J.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Perini, Fernando A.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Randall, Zachary S.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Rougier, Guillermo W.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Sargis, Eric J.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Silcox, Mary T.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Simmons, Nancy B.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Spaulding, Michelle", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Velazco, Pa\u00fal M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Weksler, Marcelo", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Wible, John R.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Cirranello, Andrea L.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "ba